  "name": "Hall Sensor LED Trigger",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Hall Sensor LED Trigger",
    "description": "USB splits at a T: center column 470Ω → SIG T → LED branch; east column 10kΩ pull-up to the Hall (+ north, − south at 0°). With no magnet the pull-up holds SIG high and the LED stays off; when the Hall pulls SIG low, the LED snaps on. Use either SIG face (west or east) on the Hall tile. Compare lesson 49 (detection) and lesson 52 (magnet polarity). Hall at 0°; LED at 90°."
  },
